## Quick Start

{% if model_source == "local" %}
1. Edit `model_definition.py` with your model logic
2. Update `deployment_config.yaml` with your variable names and transformations
3. Run the deployment:

```bash
pl run --config deployment_config.yaml --debug --one-shot
```

4. To publish data to the system:

```bash
pl run --config deployment_config.yaml --publish
```
{% elif model_source == "mlflow" %}
1. Update `env.json` with your MLflow tracking URI and credentials
2. Update `deployment_config.yaml` with your model name/version and variable names
3. Install model requirements and run:

```bash
pl run --config deployment_config.yaml -r -e env.json && pl run --config deployment_config.yaml --publish -e env.json
```
{% endif %}

## Configuration

- `deployment_config.yaml` — Main deployment configuration (interfaces, transformers, model)
- `env.json` — Environment variables (MLflow credentials, etc.)
{% if model_source == "local" %}
- `model_definition.py` — Local model definition with `ModelFactory` and model class
{% endif %}

## Validate Configuration

```bash
